# ABI Conventions

## Capitalize the acronym

The `ABI` acronym is always uppercase in identifiers — never `Abi`. Name ABI
constants in SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE ending in `_ABI`.

```ts
// ❌ BAD
export const tokenAAbi = [ /* ... */ ] as const;

// ✅ GOOD
export const TOKEN_A_ABI = [ /* ... */ ] as const;
```

## Always include the whole ABI

Embed the contract's COMPLETE ABI, copied verbatim from the compiled artifact
(`contracts/out/<Name>.sol/<Name>.json` → `.abi`). Do NOT hand-pick a subset of
functions — you will inevitably need more later (e.g. `approve`, `allowance`).

- Keep `as const` so wagmi/viem can infer argument and return types.
- One file per contract under `src/lib/abis/`.
